The fix is complete. Here's a summary:                                      
                                                                              
  ## Problem                                                                  
                                                                              
  The CI was failing on all Copilot agent PRs because the "Post Install uv"   
  step from copilot-setup-steps.yml was timing out. Specifically, the astral- 
  sh/setup-uv@v5 action's post-action cleanup runs uv cache prune --ci, which 
  consistently exceeded the 5-minute timeout and failed with exit code 2.     
                                                                              
  ## Root Cause                                                               
                                                                              
  The uv cache prune operation takes too long to complete in the CI           
  environment after the Copilot agent has installed packages (aurelian, jinja2-
  cli, wrapt). The cache grows during the agent's operations, and pruning it  
  exceeds the timeout.                                                        
                                                                              
  ## Fix                                                                      
                                                                              
  Added prune-cache: false to the astral-sh/setup-uv@v5 action configuration  
  in                                                                          
  .github/workflows/copilot-setup-steps.yml. Since this is a transient CI     
  environment with no cache persistence between runs, pruning the cache serves
  no purpose and can safely be disabled.                                      
                                                                              
  ## Security Summary                                                         
                                                                              
  • No security vulnerabilities were introduced by this change                
  • CodeQL analysis found 0 alerts                                            
  • The change only modifies CI configuration to disable an unnecessary cache 
  cleanup step

